Requirements

  Linux:

      ** Python >= 2.7 
      ** wxpython >= 2.8


  Windows:

      ** Python >= 2.7 
     
      ** pywin32 (<http://sourceforge.net/projects/pywin32/files/>) is required.  

  Mac OS X:

      ** Python >= 2.7 
        

Installation

  
  * ArchLinux:


  * Debian and Ubuntu:
  

  * FreeBSD, Gentoo
    

  * Win32
    

  * Other
    As with other Python packages, the standard way of installing from source
    is:

    python2 setup.py install (or sudo python2 setup.py install)

The app provide a way to try to install dependencies and run without that user have to install the app manually, 
Just use make for example on linux:

  
  Without sudo (Eg: Debian or Archlinux)

  [armando@archlinux ~]$ su
  [armando@archlinux ~]$ chmod u+x make-linux.sh    
  [armando@archlinux ~]$ sh make-linux.sh

  With sudo (Eg: Ubuntu)

  [armando@archlinux ~]$ sudo chmod u+x make-linux.sh  
  [armando@archlinux ~]$ sudo sh make-linux.sh  

NOTE: If you have installed Python >= 2.7, the best way to install the app is run:

  python2 setup.py install (or sudo python2 setup.py install)